IDENTITY
→ name: DIAS
→ description: Distributed Immersive Audiobook System — produzione automatizzata di audiolibri cinematografici con AI locale
→ repo: S3ph1r/dias (da creare)
→ stack: Python, Redis, Google Gemini API (Flash-Lite), Qwen3-TTS 1.7B, AudioCraft MusicGen, FFmpeg 7.0+
→ blueprint: docs/blueprint.md

ARCHITECTURE
→ overview: Pipeline sequenziale a 7 stadi. Ogni stadio consuma da una coda Redis, processa atomicamente, e produce output nella coda successiva. Un solo modello AI in VRAM alla volta.
→ structure:
  src/common/                — config, redis client, logging, base classes
  src/stage_a_ingestion/     — TextIngester (CPU — PDF/EPUB → blocchi testo)
  src/stage_b_macro_analysis/ — MacroAnalyzer (API — analisi emotiva)
  src/stage_c_scene_director/ — SceneDirector (API — audio script per scena)
  src/stage_d_voice_gen/     — VoiceGenerator (GPU — TTS con voice cloning)
  src/stage_e_music_gen/     — MusicGenerator (GPU — colonna sonora adattiva)
  src/stage_f_mixing/        — AudioMixer (CPU — FFmpeg filter_complex)
  src/stage_g_mastering/     — MasteringEngine (CPU — loudness + metadata)
  config/                    — configurazione yaml
  schemas/                   — JSON schemas per validazione inter-stadio
  docker/                    — Dockerfile per Brain e GPU Worker
  tests/                     — test per componente

INFRASTRUCTURE
→ containers:
  CT120 (192.168.1.120) — Brain: Redis + stadi CPU (A, B, C, F, G) — 4096MB, 4 CPU, 30GB — Debian 12.12 — DEPLOYED
→ external:
  GPU Worker — PC gaming Win11 sulla stessa rete — RTX 5060 Ti 16GB VRAM, 32GB RAM — stadi GPU (D, E) — on-demand
→ storage:
  NFS share tra Brain e GPU Worker per audio assets
  Path convention: /storage/audio/{voice|music|output}/{book_id}/

COMPONENTS
→ A: TextIngester     — CPU   — Estrazione testo e split in blocchi (Marker/PyMuPDF)
→ B: MacroAnalyzer    — API   — Analisi emotiva dei blocchi (Gemini Flash-Lite, max 1 call/30s)
→ C: SceneDirector    — API   — Segmentazione in scene + audio script (Gemini Flash-Lite)
→ D: VoiceGenerator   — GPU   — TTS con direzione emotiva (Qwen3-TTS 1.7B, ~7GB VRAM)
→ E: MusicGenerator   — GPU   — Colonna sonora per scena (AudioCraft MusicGen Small, ~4GB VRAM)
→ F: AudioMixer       — CPU   — Mix voice + music + SFX con ducking (FFmpeg)
→ G: MasteringEngine   — CPU   — Concatenazione, loudness -16 LUFS, MP3 320kbps + metadata

